\{s_n\}_{n\in \mathbb{Z}^+}
s_n=\sqrt{n\pi}
F(s_n) \\ =\sum_{i=0}^{n-1} \int_{\sqrt{i\pi}}^{\sqrt{(i+1)\pi}} \sin t^2 dt \\ ≦\pi \sum_{i=0}_{n-1} (-1)^i (\sqrt{i+1} - \sqrt{i})
A\triangleq \lim_{n\to\infty} F(s_n)
\epsilon>0
N\in \mathbb{N}
n≧N \Rightarrow |F(s_n) - A| <\epsilon
\frac{1}{\epsilon} < s_n
n≧N
y>s_n
|F(y)-F(s_n)|< \frac{1}{s_n} < \epsilon
|F(y) - A| < \epsilon
\lim_{y\to\infty} F(y) = A
